WEBVTT

00:12:29.280 --> 00:12:33.416
In fact, two of the original strangers
they gave the experimenter to got married.

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:35.296
(Laughter)

00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:37.856
So it's not a bad way
to generate closeness.

00:12:37.880 --> 00:12:40.833
Maybe you've got to be careful
who you do that experiment with.

00:12:40.857 --> 00:12:42.656
AG: Why do we get this backward then?

00:12:42.680 --> 00:12:45.376
DC: Because in the modern world,
in our work environment,

00:12:45.400 --> 00:12:46.781
it's a high-risk environment.

00:12:46.805 --> 00:12:50.136
We don't want to betray
a lack of competence or confidence.

00:12:50.160 --> 00:12:51.736
So, there's a natural --

00:12:51.760 --> 00:12:54.616
We are status-oriented creatures.

00:12:54.640 --> 00:12:56.616
We want to protect our status.

00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:59.176
And so we default to that a lot.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.696
If we're in a social situation,